5. Summary and Outlook
"The estimated primary mass based on the depth of shower maximum ğ‘‹max, an observable derived from
the electromagnetic component of showers, is at odds with estimations based on the muonic component. A
compilation of analyses made possible with the hybrid capabilities of the Pierre Auger Observatory were
presented here and indicate a deficit in the number of muons predicted by hadronic interaction models."
